      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "# Latest AI News — Top Stories\n\nHere's a roundup of the most significant AI developments from the past few days:\n\n## ⚖️ Musk vs. OpenAI Trial Underway\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The civil trial between the tech billionaires kicked off Monday and could help define the future of artificial intelligence. The trial is scheduled to run for four weeks, with a cast of prominent tech executives set to take the stand."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Musk was at times boastful and snarky, using the witness stand to attack Sam Altman and as a platform to score points against other tech rivals. Musk claimed Altman betrayed the original principles of OpenAI to remain a nonprofit and that the company benefited from his money and connections."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Jury selection wrapped Monday; Musk testified Tuesday in the $134B suit to return OpenAI's assets to the nonprofit and oust Altman. The case will set the legal template for what counts as a \"for-profit conversion\" in AI for the next decade."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- Notably, "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Musk admitted under oath that xAI distilled OpenAI's models to train Grok"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": ".\n\n## 🛡️ Pentagon's AI Push\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Google joins OpenAI in allowing the Pentagon to use its AI systems, as rival Anthropic remains embroiled in a court battle after seeking stronger safeguards."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The Pentagon signed classified AI deals with 7 companies, excluding Anthropic."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## 💰 Big Money & Market Moves\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Google is committing US$40bn to its AI rival Anthropic, as the firm looks to secure cloud dominance and fuel the expansion of Gen AI infrastructure."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The AI infrastructure arms race hits full throttle as Alphabet breaks away with a 63% surge in Google Cloud revenue to US$20bn for Q1 2026."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "AI Chipmaker Cerebras is said to target up to $4 Billion in IPO, and Apple raised the Mac Mini's starting price to $799 after AI frenzy drained supply."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "OpenAI missed revenue targets — Oracle and chip stocks dragged with it."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n## 🌏 Global AI Developments\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Huawei expects AI chip revenue to hit $12B in 2026, up 60%, as ByteDance and Alibaba race to secure Ascend 950PR supply."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n- "
      },
      {
